snippet.textDisplay: I love when franchises continue to grow and become better with age and time, and Pokemon is no exception. Yes it has a few flaws here and there, but when they lead to things like this, it is worth the trek along that long road up to this point in time. Pokemon has endured on charm and simplicity. That's not something a great deal of other franchises can really claim. I hope for Pokemon to stay around for many more years to come. And when it's time to bring the franchise to its end, I want Ash's final battle to be against his father, and there better be a scene showing off a clip from EVERY episode up to that moment. That would make for the ultimate sendoff.
